title: Vaqueros in pro baseball, 10/11/15
text: Vaqueros in pro baseball, 10/11/15 Staff Reports Casa Grande Valley Newspapers Inc. Final 2015 major league statistics of former Central Arizona College players (source: baseball-reference.com ): -- Ian Kinsler, IF, Detroit Tigers — .296 batting average in 154 games (624 at-bats), 73 RBIs, 35 doubles, 7 triples, 11 home runs, 10 stolen bases. -- A.J. Schugel, RHP, Arizona Diamondbacks — 0-0 record in 5 games, 5.00 ERA, 5 strikeouts and 5 walks in 9.0 innings pitched. Final 2015 minor league statistics of former Central Arizona College players (source: baseball-reference.com ): -- A.J. Schugel, RHP, Reno of the AAA Pacific Coast League and Mobile of the AA Southern League (Arizona Diamondbacks) — 9-9 record in 21 games (21 starts), 4.84 ERA, 79 strikeouts and 32 walks in 115.1 innings pitched. -- Matt Pagnozzi, C, Reno of the AAA Pacific Coast League and Mobile of the AA Southern League (Arizona Diamondbacks) — .250 batting average in 73 games (204 at-bats), 20 RBIs, 8 doubles, 1 triple, 4 home runs. -- Eric Wooten, LHP, Scranton/Wilkes-Barre of the AAA International League, Trenton of the AA Eastern League and Tampa of the A+ Florida State League (New York Yankees) — 3-8 record in 28 games (15 starts), 4.28 ERA, 89 strikeouts and 36 walks in 115.2 innings pitched. -- Jim Patterson, LHP, Durham of the AAA International League, Montgomery of the AA Southern League and Rays of the rookie Gulf Coast League (Tampa Bay Rays) — 1-1 record in 9 games (3 starts), 3.48 ERA, 17 strikeouts and three walks in 20.2 innings pitched; Bridgeport of the independent Atlantic League — 2-2 record in 12 games, 5.02 ERA, 16 strikeouts and 5 walks in 14.1 innings pitched. -- Jorge Flores, IF, New Hampshire of the AA Eastern League (Toronto Blue Jays) — .276 batting average in 123 games (395 at-bats), 28 RBIs, 20 doubles, 1 triple, 2 home runs, 10 stolen bases. -- Xorge Carrillo, C, Binghamton of the AA Eastern League (New York Mets) — .240 batting average in 94 games (325 at-bats), 40 RBIs, 14 doubles, 1 triple, 10 home runs, 1 stolen base. -- Keenan Walker, OF, Birmingham of the AA Southern League and Winston-Salem of the A+ Carolina League (Chicago White Sox) — .226 batting average in 113 games (367 at-bats), 33 RBIs, 8 doubles, 4 triples, 2 home runs, 37 stolen bases. -- Mark Shannon, OF, Arkansas of the AA Texas League, Inland Empire of the A+ California League and Angels of the rookie Arizona League (Los Angeles Angels) — .206 batting average in 41 games (141 at-bats), 14 RBIs, 2 doubles, 1 triple, 3 stolen bases. -- Fernando Perez, IF, Lake Elsinore of the A+ California League (San Diego Padres) — .224 batting average in 113 games (446 at-bats), 53 RBIs, 21 doubles, 3 triples, 10 home runs, 1 stolen base. -- Jordan Kipper, RHP, Inland Empire of the A+ California League (Los Angeles Angels) — 6-12 record in 26 games (26 starts), 5.62 ERA, 95 strikeouts and 39 walks in 128.0 innings pitched. -- David Masters, IF, Potomac of the A+ Carolina League and Hagerstown of the A South Atlantic League (Washington Nationals) — .226 batting average in 109 games (354 at-bats), 37 RBIs, 13 doubles, 1 triple, 2 home runs, 3 stolen bases. -- Brock Dykxhoorn, RHP, Quad Cities of the A Midwest League (Houston Astros) — 8-5 record in 22 games (18 starts), 3.88 ERA, 94 strikeouts and 26 walks in 109.0 innings pitched. -- Sean Hurley, OF, Vancouver of the A- Northwest League (Toronto Blue Jays) — .253 batting average in 70 games (245 at-bats), 33 RBIs, 11 doubles, 4 triples, 9 home runs, 5 stolen bases. -- Nicco Blank, RHP, Brooklyn of the A- New York-Pennsylvania League (New York Mets) — 0-5 record with 1 save in 20 games (2 starts), 2.40 ERA, 40 strikeouts and 18 walks in 41.1 innings pitched. -- Jess Amedee, RHP, Bristol of the rookie Appalachian League (Pittsburgh Pirates) — 2-0 record with 2 saves in 18 games, 3.64 ERA, 45 strikeouts and 13 walks in 29.2 innings pitched. -- Coco Johnson, OF, Windy City of the independent Frontier League — .271 batting average in 94 games (391 at-bats), 32 RBIs, 26 doubles, 2 triples, 10 home runs, 30 stolen bases. -- Zach Dando, RHP, Grand Prairie of the independent American Association — 5-8 record with 6 saves in 38 games (9 starts), 4.07 ERA, 45 strikeouts and 29 walks in 86.1 innings pitched. -- Jason Urquidez, RHP, Lancaster of the independent Atlantic League — 0-0 record with 2 saves in 4 games, 0.00 ERA, 7 strikeouts and 1 walk in 4.0 innings pitched. Final 2015 foreign league statistics of former Central Arizona College players (source: baseball-reference.com ): -- Tony Barnette, RHP, Yakult of the Japan Central League — 3-1 record with 41 saves in 59 games, 1.29 ERA, 56 strikeouts and 19 walks in 62.2 innings pitched. -- Mario Mendoza, RHP, Tijuana of the Mexican League — 3-3 record with 7 saves in 57 games, 2.50 ERA, 25 strikeouts and 14 walks in 50.1 innings pitched. -- Jason Urquidez, RHP, Tijuana of the Mexican League — 1-5 record in 25 games (3 starts), 5.67 ERA, 28 strikeouts and 15 walks in 33.1 innings pitched.
